WEBVTT

00:02:28.880 --> 00:02:31.640
to make us feel less alone.

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:34.136
And it was not long after that

00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:35.936
that I started to notice sonder

00:02:35.960 --> 00:02:40.256
being used earnestly
in conversations online,

00:02:40.280 --> 00:02:43.176
and not long after I actually noticed it,

00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:46.696
I caught it next to me
in an actual conversation in person.

00:02:46.720 --> 00:02:49.176
There is no stranger feeling
than making up a word

00:02:49.200 --> 00:02:53.496
and then seeing it
take on a mind of its own.

00:02:53.520 --> 00:02:55.616
I don't have a word
for that yet, but I will.

00:02:55.640 --> 00:02:57.056
(Laughter)

00:02:57.080 --> 00:02:58.280
I'm working on it.

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:02.280
I started to think
about what makes words real,